APF must do ALL of the following IN ORDER for the envelope to be browser-visible: (1) Send HTTP/2 HEADERS frame with :status=200, content-type=text/event-stream, access-control-allow-origin=* (or mirror origin), cache-control=no-cache. (2) Send DATA frame(s) with the complete envelope bytes (data:{...}

event:complete
data:{...}

). (3) Send END_STREAM flag WITH the last DATA frame (not separately, not RST_STREAM). (4) NEVER use RST_STREAM or GOAWAY for blocked responses that are meant to deliver an envelope ??those terminate the stream before body readable by fetch(). Also BLOCK THE RETRY: APF must prevent qianwen's automatic retry by sending the envelope on EVERY blocked attempt (not just the first), OR by injecting a response body that tells qianwen frontend to stop retrying (e.g. with audit_info.problem_code='blocked').
